				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Aria quests<a name="73656"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 25 05 12:11 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><a target="_new" href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=3682&amp;source=Live">Aria of Asceticism</a> and
<br />
<a target="_new" href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=3681&amp;source=Live">Aria of Innocence</a>
<br />
are the only two songs of their type that we get.  They are, however (IMO) very worth getting.
<br />

<br />
I use the the cure poison/disease a <b>lot</b> on myself in LDoN when I trigger traps on myself (I usually find traps by triggering them and then disarming them after-the-fact <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-4.gif" border="0" alt="Tongue out" hspace="2" />).  I've also used the remove curse song on botched LDoN chest attempts by priest classes (which seems to happen more than I thought likely).
<br />

<br />
Equipping a wind instrument <b>DOES</b> seem to increase the number of disease/poison/curse counters removed too, though, so that is an added bonus.
<br />

<br />
These two songs are <b>definitely</b> worth buying LoY and doing the quests for them, IMO.  <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> 
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
