				<td colspan="2"><span>I think you can do it solo.  I did, and I think I was under 63 at the time because I don't remember having Fading Memories AA as a safety net at the time.  I found &quot;a crazed miner&quot; in one of the locations listed in <a target="_new" href="http://www.eqdiva.com/EQ/Guide.aspx?id=91&amp;ForumID=132">this guide</a> (yes, there are some broken TCH links in that guide now).  The &quot;a crazed miner&quot; was non-aggro when I did it, and I went up to him while invis and stood almost right on top of him.  I dropped invis before I did the hand-in to him and I didn't draw any aggro from the mobs around him.  After I did the turn-in, I invised back up and left the mines.
<br />

<br />
It shouldn't be tough for you to do solo, but look at it this way:  Worst case scenario, you get killed and your corpse is less than 200pp to summon in the Guild Lobby (provided you have DoN expansion).  On my server, there are usually some nice Clerics with clicky rez that are willing to rez for free or small donation.
<br />

<br />
Corpse summoning in the new Guild Lobby should make <b>ALL</b> of us braver to do things we wouldn't consider doing in the past.  Heck, even PoFear shouldn't be <b>that</b> scary anymore for folks to try soloing their Amy Whip (for Epic 1.0).
<br />

<br />
Honestly, though, if you are careful, you shouldn't even have to worry about getting your bard killed in the mines.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
